  "instructions": [
    "Mix wheat flour and water until smooth. Cook in a pan over medium heat until thickened.",
    "In a separate pan, sauté garlic and onion with a pinch of salt until translucent.",
    "Add tomato paste, red pepper flakes (smoked), cumin powder, and coriander powder to the cooked mixture. Stir well.",
    "Pour the thickened wheat sauce into the pan with spices. Bring to a simmer and let cook for about 5 minutes or until the sauce is smooth and dense.",
    "Serve hot over your choice of rice, injera, or as a side dish."
